{
  "stem": "14251.5",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But anyway, she went to work for Ronia, the woman judge, who had to condemn so many each week, and I'm still at the orphanage.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Then my mother got sick, only I didn't know that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The hospital was right behind the orphanage, but no one said.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "You know, this is Russia.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "If you ever saw you know, chance meetings come back again.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "My mother didn't show up for what seemed like months, but it was probably six weeks or so or something.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I just figured it was over.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "She was working for the Russian judge and the baby, and the husband was an actor.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "The judge would cry herself in her bed every Sunday to make up for all the wrongly condemned people, because it wasn't a true court.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "It was-- you know, this is how you secure labor.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "All of the soldiers that came back from World War II got condemned in those courts because there was no work for them.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And this is how you get Siberian cities built that you see in today.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] One day-- I had resigned myself.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "My mother used to come every other Sunday, or I'd meet her at a park where I'd go down the street from the orphanage.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I remember we'd been to a movie.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I had never seen a film.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "We-- that meant a Tarzan movie on a primitive little screen, kind of like what we have right here, and we sat on the floor.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And it was Tarzan without sound, Tarzan swimming-- swinging from vines.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And we came down the street, and what was so horrid, it was always, the orphans are coming.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "It was disgusting.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "The orphans must have been a disgusting thing.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
